---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base>
  <header>
    <h1>Corey Woodcox</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Senior Software Engineer · Civic Technologist · Single Dad</p>
    <p class="location muted mono">Herriman, Utah &mdash; via Montréal</p>
  </header>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <div class="label">About</div>
    <div class="stack-lg">
      <p>
        Senior Software Engineer at <a href="https://www.covermymeds.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CoverMyMeds</a>.
        Ten years in healthcare tech, which has given me opinions about both software and American healthcare.
        I&rsquo;ve stopped keeping them to myself.
      </p>
      <p>
        FAA Part 107 pilot. Amateur radio operator. Wyoming roots, Utah present,
        a decade in Montréal somewhere in the middle. Utah Democratic precinct chair &mdash;
        ran unopposed; the Obama medal meme felt appropriate. Motorcycle builder when the garage cooperates.
        Fluent in French. Somehow my poutine opinions are not my hottest takes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <div class="label">Current Work</div>
    <ul class="stack-lg">
      <li class="project">
        <h3><a href="https://github.com/cwoodcox/on-record" target="_blank" rel="noopener">on-record</a></h3>
        <p>
          An MCP server wrapping Utah legislative lookup. Helps constituents identify their
          state legislators and draft personalized advocacy letters. Built because the official
          tooling is embarrassing and civic participation shouldn&rsquo;t require a law degree.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="project">
        <h3><a href="https://burrn.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BURRN</a></h3>
        <p>
          Founding member of Brave Utahns Rapid Response Network &mdash; a cross-partisan grassroots
          org that fought the legislative effort to repeal Prop 4, Utah&rsquo;s independent redistricting
          initiative. Spent hours standing next to canvassers gathering signatures. The petition failed.
          Democracy: 1, Legislature: 0 (this round).
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="project">
        <h3>Field Organizing</h3>
        <p>
          Contact data workflows using ArcGIS Online for canvassing operations.
          GIS is just geography with better PR. Also: occasionally the canvasser.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <div class="label">Elsewhere</div>
    <ul class="stack links">
      <li><a href="https://github.com/cwoodcox" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.threads.com/@cwoodcox" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Threads</a></li>
      <li><a href="/now">What I&rsquo;m doing now &rarr;</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  header {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .tagline {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .location {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .project h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .project p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.925rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .links li + li {
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }
</style>
